The heavy snow transforms Saihanba in north China's Hebei Province into a world of white. The trees with their bare branches stand out conspicuously. The yellow larches, green Mongol Scotch pines and white birches intermingle to form a unique range of winter hues. About 'Journeys in Nature': Hebei series Hebei Province hosts the largest forest park in northern China, Saihanba National Forest Park, and the country's largest expanse of coastal sand dunes, the Golden Coast National Nature Reserve. Here, you will find unique landforms and a rich variety of plants and animals. For more: Hebei series | Episode 1: Beautiful Highland Hebei series | Episode 2: Boundary River Hebei series | Episode 3: Wetland in the Snow (Cover image via a screenshot) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)